## **How to use:**

9. Click RE Extension extension button ![][image7], click Visit LinkedIn page or open [https://www.linkedin.com/feed/](https://www.linkedin.com/feed/) this page  
   ![][image8]  
10. Click RE Extension again and insert your personal email and password of the CRM and press Sign in button:![][image9]  
    Check that you are open on the [https://www.linkedin.com/feed/](https://www.linkedin.com/feed/)   
11. If you see ![][image10] you can start searching for a fit lead with Google.  
12. Before you start using RE Extension , you should copy email and a phone number from the SaleQL extension.  
13. Then on a lead profile page click Click RE Extension extension button ![][image7].  
14. After collecting data and checking information you will see result: ![][image11]  
15. Then paste the lead's email and password in the fields.  
16. You should always check is there correct information in the next fields:  
- **Lead position**. It has to be like in a CRM, you can edit it here, if you don’t know the right position, you should edit it in the CRM card after creating it.  
- **Company name** should be that, what company you are adding. If there is another company in the field, you can choose the correct company from the dropdown menu.  
- For some leads it is possible to choose another **Industry** from the dropdown menu, if it is not correct.  
- Next is very important. It’s **COMPANY LOCATION**. There must be a country where you are doing the search. Country pinned for your account in the CRM in My lead accounts.  
- If extensions haven’t found any **Facebook, Instagram, Email or Phone**, you should open the company site after adding this lead with the company, and find this information manually, if it’s available, copy it and edit the CRM card of the company with adding this types of contact information.  
17. Then click the blue button Add New Lead to CRM.

19. All the errors, what you should edit manually. You will see in the **Note** of the created CRM card. ![][image12]  
    In this example, we need to edit the lead position to Director in the Contact tab of the card. Sometimes, if you see the wrong Industry there, you should edit it.  
      
20. Then you may find and add the **next lead** of this company and run an extension. For next lead you will see this result:![][image13]
